DEPLOYING A VIRTUAL MACHINE ON CLOUD : AWS

1. Login to AWS Console

Open the AWS website and sign in to the AWS Management Console.
From the services menu, open EC2.

2. Launch a New Instance

Click on Launch Instance.
Give a name to the instance.

3. Select Machine Image

Choose an operating system:

Ubuntu Server / Amazon Linux (for Linux VM)

Windows Server (for Windows VM)

4. Choose Instance Type

Select t2.micro, which is free-tier eligible.

5. Create or Select Key Pair

Create a new key pair and download it.
This will be used to connect to the VM.

6. Configure Security Group

Allow the required ports:

SSH (port 22) → for Linux

RDP (port 3389) → for Windows

7. Launch the Instance

Click Launch Instance and wait until the status becomes “running”.

8. Connect to the VM

Linux VM: Use SSH command
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@<public-ip>

Windows VM: Download the RDP file and log in using the password.

9. Capture Details

Take screenshots of:

Instance description page

Public IP

Terminal/RDP connection screen
